Each local jurisdiction shall review its entire program and propose any necessary amendments to its entire program, including local zoning maps, at least every 6 years. Each local jurisdiction shall send in writing to the Commission, within 60 days after the completion of its review, the following information:
A statement certifying that the required review has been accomplished;
Any necessary requests for program amendments, program refinements, or other matters that the local jurisdiction wishes the Commission to consider;
An updated resource inventory; and
A statement quantifying acreages within each land classification, the growth allocation used, and the growth allocation remaining.

section.section:
In accordance with the Commission's determination in paragraph (2) of this subsection, the Commission shall:
Approve the proposed program amendment and notify the local jurisdiction;
Deny the proposed program amendment;
Approve the proposed program amendment subject to one or more conditions; or
Return the proposed program amendment to the local jurisdiction with a list of the changes to be made.

If the chairman's determination is not overridden, within 10 working days after the opportunity to override the chairman's decision under item (i) of this paragraph, the chairman, on behalf of the Commission, shall:
Determine if the program refinement is consistent with the purposes, policies, goals, and provisions of this subtitle, and all criteria of the Commission; and
A. Approve the proposed program refinement and notify the local jurisdiction;
